contents:
Pee Cueiam,
We have considered this record with special reference to the several questions presented by the specifications of error, and are not convinced that either of said specifications should be sustained. The questions involved have been so well considered and satisfactorily disposed of by the learned auditor that we think the decree should be affirmed for reasons given in his ■report.
Decree affirmed and appeal dismissed with costs to be paid by N. N. Betts, cashier, etc., appellant.
